folder: Cropsey Avenue & Bay 13th Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Cropsey Ave., south side, opposite Bay 13th Street, showing buildings belonging to the Marine and Field Club. (In 1904, this club owned 10 acres fronting on Gravesend Bay).

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing a closer view of one of the buildings.

March 1925.
